ğŸ›ï¸ 1. Background & Problem Statement

A clothing and styling E-commerce company operates both online (website + mobile app) and offline styling stores. Customers often visit physical stores for styling advice and later place orders through the app or website.
The company wants to understand which factors drive the Yearly Amount Spent (YAS) and specifically whether they should invest more into:
  Improving the mobile app,
  Enhancing the website, or
  Focusing on other customer-related metrics.

Using customer data (session behavior, membership length, usage patterns, etc.), we analyze which variables most strongly influence annual spending.

ğŸ” 2. Approach Followed
 The following workflow was used: 
  * Loaded and explored the dataset using Pandas.Ran basic EDA: distributions, pairplots, correlation checks, and patterns across features.
  * Looked closely at the main variables:
    -Avg. Session Length
    -Time on App
    -Time on Website
    -Length of Membership
  
  * Built a multivariate linear regression model to understand which features actually impact Yearly Amount Spent.
  * Split the data, trained the model, checked coefficients, and reviewed residuals to make sure the model behaved well.
  * Used the coefficient values to interpret which factors truly matter for customer spending.

